item.title: CVE-2020-5639|2024-08-04T08:39:25.369Z -- soliton%20systems%20k.k. -- filezen
item.description: Directory traversal vulnerability in FileZen versions from V3.0.0 to V4.2.2 allows remote attackers to upload an arbitrary file in a specific directory via unspecified vectors. As a result, an arbitrary OS command may be executed.
